<chapter xml:id="install.extensions" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
  <title>Installation of extensions</title>
  <sect1 xml:id="install.extensions.intro">
    <title>Introduction to Extensions</title>
    <simpara>
      HHVM supports many core extensions (including third-party). HHVM also provides an easy way through HNI (HHVM Native Interface) to create your own extensions. See the <link xlink:href="&url.hhvm.install.extensions;">full list</link>.
    </simpara>
  </sect1>
</chapter>   

